						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Rājarāja-Rājakēsarivarman (Rājarāja I), 16th year = A.D. 1001.</p>						

						<p>Gift of 96 sheep for a lamp to the temple of Maṇavāḷapperumāḷ at Tirumaṇañjēri, a part of Viḍēlviḍugu-chaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Kuṟukkai-nāḍu on the northern bank, by Māṟan Tiṭṭai of Ambar, a village in the same Nāḍu.</p>						

